mention.text: the server upstart founded four and a half years ago that came out of stealth in June 2010 with an Atom bomb : a 10U chassis crammed with 512 single - core Atom servers in a 10U chassis , all linked by a 1
The acquisition of SeaMicro , which along with Cisco Systems is one of the first new entrants in the server racket in years to actually look like it has a chance of making it

a conference call with Wall Street analysts announcing the deal after the market closed , Andrew Feldman , SeaMicro 's CEO and co - founder , said that his company had been buying Atom processors and chipsets from the distribution channel , not from Intel
